{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"425800a2-2bc1-44f5-844d-548770e9eaf3","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Update your package references** — remove `xunit.runner.visualstudio` and add `xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform`:\n\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Remove this -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n   <!-- Add this -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform\" Version=\"2.9.3\" />\n   ```\n\n2. **Enable the test platform** in your project file (or `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or run the test project directly as an executable (`dotnet run`), since Microsoft.Testing.Platform makes each test project a standalone app.\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform` version should match your `xunit` version (2.9.3).\n- `TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport` ensures `dotnet test` uses the new platform instead of VSTest.\n- No code changes are needed — your existing `[Fact]` / `[Theory]` tests work as-is.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d6a9485f-16c0-42ba-8c5d-21da559263be","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":394,"requestId":"0835:44A9F:7E16E59:8C4A184:69EABE0E"},"id":"a3ab4887-9006-46d2-8c7a-580d6c6d7010","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:49:26.741Z","parentId":"9a1abfa0-3535-4f8c-88df-7f574b4c6029"}
